        "username": "jason_stein",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jason_stein/{size}/2728_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-01-07T22:21:24.000Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Wanted to catch this wine before it closes down. Much deeper in color and aromatically than the 17 Chambolle. Lively mix of dark berries spread across a well-rounded, expansive palate. After 20 min in the glass vosne spice comes out in spades. Very youthful at this point obviously but will become something special with time. I will be sitting on the remainder of my bottles.</p>",
