      {
        "id": 2786979,
        "name": "jason stein",
        "username": "jason_stein",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/jason_stein/{size}/2728_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-01-08T01:48:34.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"4\" data-topic=\"157400\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>We had this and the Chambolle in a small 2017 horizontal about a month ago, and it showed really well. I think most of us agreed it was stronger than the CM. Two other excellent wines in our tasting were Bertheau Chambolle Villages and Faiveley Mercurey Clos des Myglands.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Have been pleased with the 17s I\u2019ve tried thus far. Agree that the Vosne villages is a stronger wine this year, but the Chambolle is very charming in its own right, just far lighter, and it will likely come into maturity sooner.</p>",
