        "created_at": "2020-01-08T02:23:51.000Z",
        "cooked": "<aside class=\"quote no-group quote-modified\" data-post=\"7\" data-topic=\"157400\">\n<blockquote>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-post=\"3\" data-topic=\"157400\">\n<blockquote>\n<p>Had many of his 2017s in barrel a year and a half ago, but they were hard to taste, although they seemed long and promising.  Cannot wait to taste more at the Paulee in NY in March.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>His malos are normally quite late so can be hard to taste early, I try to go towards the end of my time in Burgundy each year. You are in for a treat at La Paul\u00e9e.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>Thanks but not surprised. I am a big fan.</p>\n<p>Also, see my notes having tasted the 2017s while they were undergoing malo.  <a href=\"https://www.wineberserkers.com/forum/viewtopic.php?f=1&amp;t=153014&amp;p=2547924&amp;hilit=dublere#p2547924\" class=\"inline-onebox\">Visit to Burgundy and Champagne - WINE TALK - WineBerserkers</a></p>",
